<br>
    <h2>Vacant Research Positions:</h2>
<br>
 <p>
  Job title: Visibility Enhancement and Robust Motion Analysis in Extreme Outdoor Conditions
 </p>

  <p>
    Application deadline: 15 May 2016
  </p>
 <p>
Location: Singapore
  </p>

 <br>
   <p>
Three Research Fellow positions are available at the Department of
Electrical and Computer Engineering, National University of Singapore
(NUS). These positions are to investigate visibility enhancement and
to develop robust motion algorithms that are robust to extreme outdoor
conditions such as rain, dust, haze, as well as under night-time and
underwater conditions. The successful candidate should have a Ph.D. or
equivalent degree, and he/she should have a strong background in the
aforementioned areas, and in applied mathematics knowledge like large
scale convex optimization and sparse representation, as well as
proficiency in programming. Strong publication records in
internationally recognized conferences or journals are preferred. 
  </p>

 <p>
The positions are funded for 3 year (with possibility for renewal),
and are available immediately. Salary is competitive. Please send a
detailed CV with publication list, a concise description of research
interests and future plans, and academic transcripts to both:
  </p>

 <br>
 <p>
Dr Cheong Loong Fah<br>
Department of Electrical & Computer Engineering Faculty of Engineering<br>
4 Engineering Drive 3<br>
Singapore 117576.<br>
Email: eleclf@nus.edu.sg
  </p>

 <p>
Dr Robby Tan<br>
Yale-NUS College<br>
16 College Avenue West, #01-220<br>
Singapore 138527<br>
Email: robby.tan@yale-nus.edu.sg
  </p>

<br>
 <p>
We will begin reviewing applications for the position immediately.
<br>
<br>
